summary:
Click for better quality 
I made this as II is now over and I wanted to also share my #IImemories
~~~
God so where do I start...
body:
Click for better quality

I made this as II is now over and I wanted to also share my #IImemories

~~~

God so where do I start with my II experience. So my show was on July 15th, the Uniondale NY show. I can’t believe it’s been two months.

When I got there the line was really long but I eventually got it and went immediately to the merch line (sadly I wasn’t able to meet them). I got the marble shirt, hoodie, plushie, and poster (all good quality).

But nobody cares about that now do they, you guys wanna hear about the show right? My view of the stage can be found below but I got pretty good seats that I was happy with.

I don’t have any pictures from the show as per their wishes not to film or take pictures during the show.

The show was amazing, and even before the show too. People started a conga line down on the floor and even the security guards were dancing.

Also just a tip if you’re buying a poster buy it after the show. My first poster I bought got stolen/lost. So I suggest buying them afterwords at any show so that doesn’t happen unless you have somewhere to put it.

This show was the most fun I’ve ever had in a long time. Thank you Dan and Phil

Love,

~Hazel<3

@danielhowell

@amazingphil

(Reblogs would be appreciated💕)
